162
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:28,050
<i><‐Lieutenant,></i>

163
00:08:28,050 --> 00:08:29,480
<i><‐should we go after him with the Aries...></i>

164
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:31,080
<i><... once you return with the Leo?></i>

165
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:33,300
<i>‐We’ll head after him with a carrier</i>

166
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:34,580
<i>and catch up with him on the the ground.</i>

167
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:37,520
<i>It's our chance to find out the purpose of Operation M.</i>

168
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:39,360
<i><‐Any chance he'll blow himself up?></i>

169
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,800
‐He’s made it all the way to earth.

170
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:43,760
He’s not going to commit suicide before setting foot on it.

171
00:08:48,140 --> 00:08:55,400
[♪♪]

172
00:08:55,420 --> 00:08:57,720
<i>Zechs: He transformed into a mobile suit!</i>

173
00:08:58,230 --> 00:08:59,550
<i>‐Pilot 2: Lieutenant Zechs,</i>

174
00:08:59,610 --> 00:09:01,360
<i>what kind of machine is that?</i>

175
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,480
‐No idea.

176
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:04,360
<i>I thought only the Alliance and</i>

177
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:07,040
<i>OZ had the technology to create mobile suits.</i>

178
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:12,120
<i>‐Do it.</i>

179
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,840
He’s intense. Perhaps...!

180
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:32,600
‐It moved!

181
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,220
‐Aaaghh!

182
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:54,820
[laughs hysterically]

183
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,740
One more to go.

184
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:58,700
He blew away two Aries

185
00:09:58,710 --> 00:09:59,980
with just one shot!

186
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:01,680
Not to shabby!

187
00:10:21,940 --> 00:10:23,820
<i>‐Pilot 1:</i>

188
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:24,920
<i>‐Zechs: Yeah.</i>

189
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:25,970
<i>sorry to worry you.</i>

190
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:28,000
<i>I did everything I could.</i>

191
00:10:31,260 --> 00:10:31,880
<i>‐And?</i>

192
00:10:32,060 --> 00:10:34,260
<i><‐Judging by the strength of the mobile suit...></i>

193
00:10:34,260 --> 00:10:36,700
<i><...It could only be made from Gundanium alloy.></i>

194
00:10:36,820 --> 00:10:37,960
‐So then,

195
00:10:37,980 --> 00:10:40,280
that WAS a Gundam!

196
00:10:44,620 --> 00:10:46,700
The mobile suit might be undamaged,

197
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:49,180
but that reckless pilot won’t have survived.

198
00:10:53,610 --> 00:10:55,100
<i><...the unregistered mobile suit.></i>

199
00:10:56,820 --> 00:10:58,860
‐Let them do as they wish.

200
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:02,380
Tell them it sank in the J. A. P. point of the Asia area.

201
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:06,500
They offered to bring it up? HA!

202
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:11,140
There’s no bright future for soldiers scurrying for their reward.

203
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:25,230
Gundam Wing

204
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,320
<i>‐Mr. Darlian!</i>

205
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:35,440
<i>What was discussed at the Colony Summit?</i>

206
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:37,440
<i>‐What are the colonies' demands to the Alliance?</i>

207
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:39,440
<i>‐Any comments, Vice Foreign Minister Darlian?</i>

208
00:11:39,550 --> 00:11:41,350
<i>‐Here on Earth people are concerned about...</i>

209
00:11:41,350 --> 00:11:43,080
<i>... when the colonies will attack.</i>

210
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,720
<i>‐What do you have to say, Mr. Darlian?!</i>

211
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,960
<i>‐It’s a hostile situation with the colonies isn’t it?</i>

212
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,080
<i>Isn’t it Minister?
‐Mr Darlian people are very concerned.</i>

213
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:48,540
<i>‐Mr Darlian people are very concerned.</i>

214
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,080
<i>what kind of outcome can you predict?</i>

215
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,540
<i>do you think theres going to be a war?
‐Please Vice Foreign Minister Darlian!</i>

216
00:11:51,540 --> 00:11:52,280
<i>The press would like a statement.</i>

217
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:54,000
<i>any statement for the press?</i>

218
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,240
‐We have been waiting for you, Mr. Darlian.

219
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:59,000
A military car s waiting for you outside.

220
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,480
Please proceed quickly.

221
00:12:00,740 --> 00:12:01,660
‐Right away?

222
00:12:01,780 --> 00:12:02,960
That won’t do.

223
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:06,740
I have some things to take care of first for my daughters birthday.

224
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:09,980
<i>‐I have arranged for a separate car to take your daughter.</i>

225
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,680
‐Don’t trouble yourself about me.

226
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:15,700
I'm quite capable of finding my own way home.

227
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:17,900
‐Well. lets go then.

228
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,680
General Septem is expecting you.

229
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:32,850
[♪♪]

230
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:36,820
Father, don’t you realize my birthday is coming up soon?!

231
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:40,780
The average girl would probably flip over this.

232
00:12:44,490 --> 00:12:45,840
A military plane.

233
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:47,760
This place would have already been a space harbor...

234
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:49,030
...if it weren’t for those planes.

235
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:52,040
[sighs]

236
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,820
I guess I’ll head home.

237
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:54,860
[gasps]

238
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:58,380
A body!

239
00:13:05,210 --> 00:13:06,640
A military uniform...?

240
00:13:07,070 --> 00:13:08,280
He’s a soldier.

241
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:08,760
[grunting]

242
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,780
I better get help!

243
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:15,850
♪♪[orchetral music]

244
00:13:15,850 --> 00:13:17,340
‐You’re saying that three of your

245
00:13:17,340 --> 00:13:19,080
mobile suits were shot down?

246
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:22,400
‐It’s unlike you to be so careless.

247
00:13:22,820 --> 00:13:24,980
It will be quite an effort to calm down the...

248
00:13:24,990 --> 00:13:27,080
...Alliance big shots.

249
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:31,580
